# Character Rendering

`CharacterRenderer` is the only owner of frame-level animation. Keep its public
API stable:

- `init(host)`, `setView(partial)`, `resize()`, `destroy()`.
- The engine/layer feeds state via `setView`; it must not know how many sprite
  layers exist or how frames advance.

## Two states (all clips at 12 fps)

- `stand`: two layers - a 360x720 body and a 200x200 head pinned to the body's
  top-centre. Body either holds `body-normal` or loops a hand-gesture clip
  (`both`/`right`/`left`). Head shows a lip-sync viseme (while speaking), an
  expression, or an automatic blink.
- `move`: one 360x720 full-body clip (head + body baked in). `locomotion: 'left'`
  plays start (24) -> stride loop (12) -> stop (12) once, holding the last frame.

## Assets and lighting

- All filename/frame-list mapping lives in `visemes.ts` (`VISEME_FILE`,
  `EXPRESSION_FILE`, `BLINK`, `GESTURE_FRAMES`, `MOVE_LEFT_SEQUENCE`,
  `ALL_CHARACTER_FILES`). Add new clips there, not inline in the renderer.
- Honor lighting `character: on | off`:
  - `on` = normal palette.
  - `off` = flat silhouette in the theme background colour (filter on the root
    container, so both states are silhouetted).
- Advance frames from accumulated `deltaMS` in the ticker; only swap a texture
  when the resolved frame actually changes.
